SIMPLE: roguish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roguish
<hw>Rogu"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Vagrant.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>roguish</qex> madness⟦br⟧
Allows itself to anything.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resembling, or characteristic of, a rogue;
knavish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Pleasantly mischievous; waggish; arch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The most bewitching leer with her eyes, the most
<qex>roguish</qex> cast.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Rogu"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Rogu"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roguy</ent>⟦br⟧
